1
00:00:01,240 --> 00:00:02,970
Episode 30

2
00:00:02,970 --> 00:00:05,420
- One more photo?
- Okay.

3
00:00:07,100 --> 00:00:09,850
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

4
00:00:12,580 --> 00:00:16,580
I found this in your dressing room. This belongs to Professor Song, doesn't it?

5
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:21,900
I think it is his. I'll return it to him.

6
00:00:24,560 --> 00:00:27,050
We should take some photos, too.

7
00:00:27,050 --> 00:00:30,780
Principal, please take a photo of us.

8
00:00:34,330 --> 00:00:37,300
One, two, three.

9
00:00:39,620 --> 00:00:42,290
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

10
00:00:42,290 --> 00:00:44,520
It came out well, it looks good.

11
00:00:44,520 --> 00:00:47,050
Only you look good, what is this?

12
00:00:50,630 --> 00:00:52,360
Yi Yeong.

13
00:00:55,050 --> 00:00:59,410
I don't have any coins right now, so can you get me a drink from the vending machine?

14
00:00:59,410 --> 00:01:03,380
I'm suddenly so thirsty, I think I'll die.

15
00:01:03,380 --> 00:01:05,560
Suddenly so thirsty?

16
00:01:05,560 --> 00:01:08,880
- Sure, what do you want?
- Anything, the cheapest one.

17
00:01:08,880 --> 00:01:11,790
You always say "Anything, the cheapest one."

18
00:01:17,970 --> 00:01:20,360
He usually did that when he was lying.

19
00:01:20,360 --> 00:01:23,260
Really?

20
00:01:25,630 --> 00:01:29,660
I was there too, that day, in the lobby after the performance.

21
00:01:30,410 --> 00:01:33,090
Were you?

22
00:01:33,090 --> 00:01:37,590
Then we could have met that day.

23
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:43,000
To be honest, I couldn't watch Ian's performance until the end.

24
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:44,340
Why not?

25
00:01:44,340 --> 00:01:46,870
I got a bit jealous.

26
00:01:47,770 --> 00:01:52,620
Have I told you why I quit piano?

27
00:01:52,620 --> 00:01:54,260
No.

28
00:01:54,260 --> 00:01:56,490
It was because of Ian.

29
00:01:57,410 --> 00:02:02,520
When I hear him play, it felt meaningless

30
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:05,790
for me to continue playing piano.

31
00:02:05,790 --> 00:02:08,070
I had a hard time with that, back then.

32
00:02:08,070 --> 00:02:11,830
Thinking about it now, I don't know why I ever had such thoughts.

33
00:02:11,830 --> 00:02:15,040
In any case, I was in the car,

34
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:18,270
and went to the lobby  right after the performance ended.

35
00:02:18,270 --> 00:02:19,600
Sure, what do you want?

36
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:21,150
Anything, the cheapest one.

37
00:02:21,150 --> 00:02:24,010
You always say "Anything, the cheapest one."

38
00:02:24,010 --> 00:02:26,940
- Thanks.
- Sure.

39
00:02:26,940 --> 00:02:28,170
Oh, Hyung.

40
00:02:28,170 --> 00:02:30,680
Why are you still here, not going to the after party?

41
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:33,060
I wanted to take some photos.

42
00:02:35,290 --> 00:02:39,100
Sorry, I'm just so warm right now.

43
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:43,120
Can you please take this and my performance jacket and put it in your car?

44
00:02:44,990 --> 00:02:47,950
Right now?
- Yes, right now.-

45
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:51,490
Sure.

46
00:02:53,610 --> 00:02:55,400
Thanks.

47
00:03:06,170 --> 00:03:09,590
So that's why you had his clothes.

48
00:03:09,590 --> 00:03:14,160
I didn't go to the after party that day and went right home.

49
00:03:14,160 --> 00:03:20,880
On my way to my car, I saw our mom.

50
00:03:21,610 --> 00:03:27,020
I wasn't feeling very good and I didn't want to go to the after party.

51
00:03:27,900 --> 00:03:31,290
And Ian kept calling me,

52
00:03:31,950 --> 00:03:34,850
but I didn't answer his calls.

53
00:03:34,850 --> 00:03:38,120
I wonder what he wanted to tell me.

54
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:41,860
If I only answered his call,

55
00:03:41,860 --> 00:03:45,420
would he still have died that way?

56
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:50,180
I thought about that hundreds of times.

57
00:03:50,180 --> 00:03:52,590
Don't blame yourself anymore.

58
00:03:52,590 --> 00:03:56,630
You didn't do anything wrong that day.

59
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:05,850
Ah, about Conductor,

60
00:04:07,370 --> 00:04:11,880
on the day of the incident, I thought he was there to kill us,

61
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:15,110
but I don't think that was the case.

62
00:04:15,110 --> 00:04:17,990
He was there to rescue us.

63
00:04:17,990 --> 00:04:20,570
Rescue you?

64
00:04:23,520 --> 00:04:26,770
Please spare us, please spare us...

65
00:04:28,860 --> 00:04:33,800
I thought I removed the rope that was tying my wrists, but it wasn't me.

66
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:40,480
The Conductor cut the rope with the knife that he had.

67
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:43,150
And he told us to run away quickly.

68
00:04:43,150 --> 00:04:44,820
Run away from here.

69
00:04:44,820 --> 00:04:47,460
Who are you?

70
00:04:49,580 --> 00:04:51,870
Sunbae Ju Wan?

71
00:05:04,690 --> 00:05:07,350
Don't waste time and get out quickly!

72
00:05:08,660 --> 00:05:12,670
I reproached him so much, calling him Ian's murderer.

73
00:05:12,670 --> 00:05:15,020
But that wasn't true.

74
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:32,290
Whether he killed Ian or not, he is a murderer.

75
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:35,910
What does that mean?

76
00:05:35,910 --> 00:05:40,210
Nam Ju Wan killed Yun Yeong Gil. There is a witness.

77
00:05:40,210 --> 00:05:41,860
Is that true?

78
00:05:41,860 --> 00:05:44,160
I have the video.

79
00:05:57,680 --> 00:06:02,920
This... who sent this to you? Do the police know, too?

80
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:06,170
They will, soon. The witness even uploaded a message on a bulletin board.

81
00:06:06,170 --> 00:06:08,340
The police will investigate soon.

82
00:06:11,670 --> 00:06:14,210
I told him to turn himself in.

83
00:06:34,190 --> 00:06:40,770
But if you really killed someone, Conductor,

84
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:47,620
I wish you will turn yourself in, even now.

85
00:06:47,620 --> 00:06:52,710
Turn yourself in, I will give you an opportunity. Please tell them who really killed Ian.

86
00:06:52,710 --> 00:06:56,160
Do you want to see someone else get hurt or killed?

87
00:06:57,060 --> 00:06:59,670
Is it Hong Yi Yeong's turn next?

88
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:03,960
Please stop lying.

89
00:07:03,960 --> 00:07:07,680
You are someone I looked up to for seven years.

90
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:13,690
Where is the Conductor that I liked and respected so much?

91
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:24,380
Hong Yi Yeong

92
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:35,330
Conductor?

93
00:07:35,330 --> 00:07:38,400
Oh, how are you feeling?

94
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:40,970
I'm fine.

95
00:07:40,970 --> 00:07:47,380
I called because I have something I really wanted to tell you.

96
00:07:48,270 --> 00:07:50,160
What is it?

97
00:07:51,580 --> 00:07:54,530
I finally remembered everything.

98
00:07:54,530 --> 00:08:00,940
You didn't come to that warehouse that night to kill Kim Ian and me,

99
00:08:00,940 --> 00:08:03,760
you came to rescue us, didn't you?

100
00:08:06,330 --> 00:08:11,590
Yun showed me a video of you today.

101
00:08:11,590 --> 00:08:14,420
The video with Yun Yeong Gil.

102
00:08:15,550 --> 00:08:19,170
I don't know what other people think,

103
00:08:19,170 --> 00:08:23,790
but I am sure you did not kill Kim Ian.

104
00:08:23,790 --> 00:08:29,590
So why did such bad things happen between you and Yun Yeong Gil?

105
00:08:30,390 --> 00:08:33,820
Thinking about that makes my heart hurt so much.

106
00:08:35,990 --> 00:08:39,390
You know everything about what happened that day, don't you?

107
00:08:39,390 --> 00:08:42,930
Before more bad things happen,

108
00:08:42,930 --> 00:08:47,460
can't you help us find who killed Kim Ian?

109
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:52,900
I request your help.

110
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:56,480
I would really like

111
00:08:58,030 --> 00:09:02,760
that no more people were to be hurt or killed because of what happened that day.

112
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:22,450
Yang Su Jeong?

113
00:09:22,450 --> 00:09:25,990
- We have met once before, haven't we?
- Yes.

114
00:09:25,990 --> 00:09:28,060
We did some investigating.

115
00:09:28,060 --> 00:09:30,720
You are the one who uploaded a message on the Sinyeong Philharmonic bulletin board

116
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:34,540
with the nickname "Yu Da," aren't you?

117
00:09:34,540 --> 00:09:37,340
Saying that you are a witness to what happened that night?

118
00:09:41,020 --> 00:09:45,350
Shall we talk? And you have your cell phone with you, don't you?

119
00:09:45,350 --> 00:09:46,530
What about it?

120
00:09:46,530 --> 00:09:50,470
We have a confiscation warrant for your cell phone, Yang Su Jeong.

121
00:09:50,470 --> 00:09:54,690
We will confirm something and return it to you. Show her the warrant.

122
00:10:00,140 --> 00:10:03,790
Yang Su Jeong! Yang Su Jeong!

123
00:10:03,790 --> 00:10:05,110
Yang Su Jeong!

124
00:10:05,110 --> 00:10:08,150
Just listen to us, please.

125
00:10:08,150 --> 00:10:09,920
Yang Su Jeong!

126
00:10:09,920 --> 00:10:11,370
Yang Su Jeong!

127
00:10:11,370 --> 00:10:13,670
Out of the way, please!

128
00:10:15,230 --> 00:10:18,220
Sorry, we are sorry.

129
00:10:25,470 --> 00:10:27,670
Yang Su Jeong?

130
00:10:29,010 --> 00:10:31,570
Calm down, please.

131
00:10:44,760 --> 00:10:48,740
Why do large conglomerates need cultural foundations? Hotbeds of corruption. Who is Ms. Yun of Sinyeong Philharmonic?

132
00:10:48,740 --> 00:10:53,550
Corruption in a cultural foundation, and how an employee is involved.

133
00:10:57,620 --> 00:11:00,110
Has Ms. Yun embezzled foundation funds? Rumors that a music foundation

134
00:11:00,110 --> 00:11:02,800
for rural youth never existed. Sinyeong Philharmonic reputation ruined.

135
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:14,620
This is my notebook computer. Don't ever open it.

136
00:11:14,620 --> 00:11:17,690
It's full of all the bad things I've done here.

137
00:11:17,690 --> 00:11:20,580
If you look at it, you will come to hate me.

138
00:11:20,580 --> 00:11:24,310
Keep it for me, and throw it in the Han River when you get a chance.

139
00:11:25,770 --> 00:11:29,020
Are you really alright?

140
00:11:30,430 --> 00:11:35,790
Do I look alright? I may go to prison.

141
00:11:35,790 --> 00:11:39,170
Whatever happens to me, or whether Sinyeong Philharmonic disappears or not,

142
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:42,900
you can just go back to the U.S. You have family there.

143
00:11:43,990 --> 00:11:48,100
But not me. I have to survive somehow.

144
00:11:48,100 --> 00:11:50,010
I request this favor.

145
00:12:21,290 --> 00:12:22,860
Why are you so calm?

146
00:12:22,860 --> 00:12:25,690
There is a witness, what will you do?

147
00:12:25,690 --> 00:12:27,360
Are you thinking about turning yourself in?

148
00:12:27,360 --> 00:12:30,670
Who knows? I'm thinking about it.

149
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:35,880
How about going abroad for a while? I can send you for about three years.

150
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:37,780
I'll probably get arrested at the airport.

151
00:12:37,780 --> 00:12:41,260
So why did you let things come to this point?

152
00:12:41,260 --> 00:12:45,190
You should have given me some room to move, at the very least.

153
00:12:45,190 --> 00:12:47,390
What are you so anxious about?

154
00:12:47,390 --> 00:12:51,530
Are you afraid that if I'm arrested, you will be dragged along, too?

155
00:12:51,530 --> 00:12:53,310
Don't worry too much about that.

156
00:12:53,310 --> 00:12:56,130
Yun Yeong Gil was stalking me, he demanded money,

157
00:12:56,130 --> 00:12:59,590
we fought and he fell by accident. That's how I will take care of it.

158
00:13:00,490 --> 00:13:03,390
For the time being, don't come to see me.

159
00:13:03,390 --> 00:13:07,020
I won't be able to, even if I want to.

160
00:13:07,020 --> 00:13:11,420
There is something that I am curious about, regarding that day a year ago.

161
00:13:11,420 --> 00:13:12,980
A year ago? What now?

162
00:13:12,980 --> 00:13:16,090
You arrived in your car to the accident site on the highway, then rode in Yun Yeong Gil's car, didn't you?

163
00:13:16,090 --> 00:13:17,570
Why are you talking about this again, now?

164
00:13:17,570 --> 00:13:18,860
I was just curious.

165
00:13:18,860 --> 00:13:21,700
When Yun Yeong Gil got out of his car and chased Yi Yeong,

166
00:13:21,700 --> 00:13:24,590
weren't you riding in the back seat of his car?

167
00:13:24,590 --> 00:13:26,510
While just watching Ian after he was stabbed?

168
00:13:26,510 --> 00:13:30,810
He didn't even see your face, so why did you kill him?

169
00:13:32,670 --> 00:13:35,560
So you're really making me into a murderer, aren't you?

170
00:13:35,560 --> 00:13:38,450
Because you don't want to go down alone? Sorry,

171
00:13:38,450 --> 00:13:42,400
but the person who hit Kim Ian with the car was Yun Yeong Gil.

172
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:44,430
No.

173
00:13:44,430 --> 00:13:49,270
Yun Yeong Gil was chasing Hong Yi Yeong. I saw it.

174
00:13:49,270 --> 00:13:51,270
And the person in the car was you, Professor.

175
00:13:51,270 --> 00:13:54,800
No! What do you know?

176
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:58,960
There were five people at the site that night, weren't there?

177
00:13:58,960 --> 00:14:01,780
Yun Yeong Gil was chasing Hong Yi Yeong,

178
00:14:01,780 --> 00:14:04,540
and Ian was lying in the road, after he was stabbed.

179
00:14:04,540 --> 00:14:10,920
And I was going there. Since I didn't kill Kim Ian, it was you.

180
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:12,210
But you killed him.

181
00:14:12,210 --> 00:14:16,200
Because you appeared and he saw your face. Isn't that right?

182
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:19,900
Then why are you looking for the evidence that Yun Yeong Gil hid?

183
00:14:19,900 --> 00:14:23,480
You are afraid that your face is recorded on that.

184
00:14:23,480 --> 00:14:26,970
Because you ran over a living person with a car.

185
00:14:26,970 --> 00:14:30,750
Why did you kill him? He didn't know anything.

186
00:14:30,750 --> 00:14:33,670
Even if he saw your face, he wouldn't have done anything.

187
00:14:33,670 --> 00:14:35,780
Don't act big, when you're the one who doesn't know anything.

188
00:14:35,780 --> 00:14:39,020
That day, he threatened me first, got it?

189
00:14:39,020 --> 00:14:43,340
Why it was me getting out of the car? Was it me who was doing this to them?

190
00:14:43,340 --> 00:14:45,520
He asked if other people knew

191
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:48,640
that I'm going around doing such things.

192
00:14:48,640 --> 00:14:50,830
He asked me that while smirking!

193
00:14:54,350 --> 00:14:57,090
Is that why you killed him?

194
00:14:57,090 --> 00:14:58,960
Yes. I killed him.

195
00:14:58,960 --> 00:15:02,430
Why? Going to throw me in prison or something?

196
00:15:04,670 --> 00:15:09,600
I'm regretting to death that I can't see that for myself.

197
00:15:18,050 --> 00:15:19,930
Conductor Nam Ju Wan.

198
00:15:19,930 --> 00:15:25,020
Why are you doing this now, after being quiet for a year?

199
00:15:25,020 --> 00:15:30,040
You were insisting that you didn't kill Yun Yeong Gil, but are you now scared because there is a witness?

200
00:15:30,040 --> 00:15:34,470
You just don't want to go down alone? Are you going to drag me in and confess to our crimes together?

201
00:15:34,470 --> 00:15:40,140
And if you do, does that somehow mitigate your committing murder?

202
00:15:40,140 --> 00:15:42,660
If you confess or not, that is your choice.

203
00:15:42,660 --> 00:15:47,900
But I will never become Kim Ian's murderer like you want.

204
00:15:47,900 --> 00:15:49,540
Why not?

205
00:15:50,760 --> 00:15:55,450
Because there is a witness for your crime, but there is no evidence for mine.

206
00:15:55,450 --> 00:15:57,290
Is that unfair?

207
00:15:57,290 --> 00:16:00,190
The world is unfair.

208
00:16:00,190 --> 00:16:05,820
So don't exert yourself needlessly, just go home and wait for the police.

209
00:16:06,560 --> 00:16:12,410
Before I accuse of you of killing Kim Ian a year ago, too.

210
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:44,630
Hold on, hold on.

211
00:16:56,160 --> 00:16:58,730
Conductor, did you really ...

212
00:17:00,990 --> 00:17:03,660
kill Yun Yeong Gil?

213
00:17:09,350 --> 00:17:11,160
Yes.

214
00:17:13,640 --> 00:17:15,660
How?

215
00:17:15,660 --> 00:17:19,440
He came right before the performance to demand money.

216
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:24,650
We fought physically and I pushed him, which caused him to fall down the stairs.

217
00:17:24,650 --> 00:17:30,750
You even killed someone. What do you have to say to me?

218
00:17:34,390 --> 00:17:37,890
I wanted to tell you what happened that day.

219
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:40,010
That day?

220
00:17:40,010 --> 00:17:43,170
A year ago, the day Ian died.

221
00:17:43,170 --> 00:17:47,190
Why are you telling me that now? What use is it now?

222
00:17:47,190 --> 00:17:50,820
You killed someone.

223
00:17:50,820 --> 00:17:56,190
Are you about to tell me that you killed Kim Ian, too, perhaps?

224
00:17:57,230 --> 00:18:01,960
No. Can't you just hear me out?

225
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:06,620
I feel you are the only one who will believe me. I request this of you.

226
00:18:08,350 --> 00:18:12,840
After the performance that day, I saw Kang Myeong Seok meeting with Yun Yeong Gil.

227
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:15,650
Professor Kang told him to find the ballpoint pen he had lost,

228
00:18:15,650 --> 00:18:19,880
and that Hong Yi Yeong and Kim Ian had taken it.

229
00:18:19,880 --> 00:18:24,750
I already knew Yun Yeong Gil was dangerous, so I followed him,

230
00:18:24,750 --> 00:18:27,380
and saw him come out of a warehouse.

231
00:18:27,380 --> 00:18:31,290
And you went inside?

232
00:18:31,290 --> 00:18:36,940
Yes. I thought I should help free those two kids.

233
00:18:36,940 --> 00:18:40,350
That was when things began to get twisted.

234
00:18:40,350 --> 00:18:41,540
Twisted?

235
00:18:41,540 --> 00:18:45,130
From this point on, I just heard about it, because I didn't see it.

236
00:18:45,130 --> 00:18:49,010
Yi Yeong ran away with the knife that I had dropped.

237
00:18:50,870 --> 00:18:52,570
It's dangerous!

238
00:18:55,740 --> 00:18:58,570
And Ian was stabbed with it.

239
00:18:58,570 --> 00:19:01,610
When I finally got to the scene,

240
00:19:02,470 --> 00:19:05,370
Ian's dead body was there.

241
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:19,610
Who killed him?

242
00:19:19,610 --> 00:19:23,490
I don't know, because I didn't see it.

243
00:19:23,490 --> 00:19:26,690
Until now, all I had was a suspicion.

244
00:19:27,890 --> 00:19:32,480
But now? You know who it was?

245
00:19:36,040 --> 00:19:38,480
I have a request of you.

246
00:19:48,180 --> 00:19:49,510
What is it?

247
00:19:49,510 --> 00:19:52,450
This is a key for the last locker in our waiting room.

248
00:19:52,450 --> 00:19:57,420
If something happens to me, please give what's in that locker to Jang Yun.

249
00:19:58,200 --> 00:19:59,670
What will happen?

250
00:19:59,670 --> 00:20:04,480
I don't know when we will meet again. But on that day,

251
00:20:05,100 --> 00:20:07,390
let's see each other with a smile.

252
00:20:24,520 --> 00:20:26,750
It's sweet.

253
00:20:26,750 --> 00:20:28,600
Yes, it's yummy.

254
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:30,660
Is Uncle alright?

255
00:20:30,660 --> 00:20:32,790
Don't worry about him.

256
00:20:32,790 --> 00:20:36,230
Oh, look at that, you will get a scar.

257
00:20:36,230 --> 00:20:39,920
Here, let me see.

258
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:41,160
No, no.

259
00:20:41,160 --> 00:20:43,580
Just leave it.

260
00:20:49,430 --> 00:20:51,560
Conductor?

261
00:21:20,840 --> 00:21:24,150
Conductor Nam Ju Wan

262
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:40,810
What's going on?

263
00:21:43,830 --> 00:21:47,080
I heard Hong Yi Yeong got hurt while rescuing someone?

264
00:21:47,080 --> 00:21:48,690
Yes.

265
00:21:48,690 --> 00:21:53,580
She is as nosy as ever. Is she badly hurt?

266
00:21:53,580 --> 00:21:55,520
A bit.

267
00:21:55,520 --> 00:21:59,300
If she had broken a leg or something, I would have felt refreshed.

268
00:21:59,300 --> 00:22:01,880
How can you say such a thing?

269
00:22:01,880 --> 00:22:04,070
What do you want?

270
00:22:10,100 --> 00:22:13,320
Conductor asked me to give this to you.

271
00:22:14,230 --> 00:22:15,320
What is this?

272
00:22:15,320 --> 00:22:19,760
It's the key to the last locker in the waiting room at Sinyeong Philharmonic.

273
00:22:19,760 --> 00:22:24,120
That day, a year ago, what Conductor saw

274
00:22:24,120 --> 00:22:27,520
was Kim Ian's dead body.

275
00:22:29,360 --> 00:22:33,110
He did not see who killed Kim Ian.

276
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:40,280
How about trusting him, just this once?

277
00:22:53,050 --> 00:22:55,240
Nam Ju Wan?

278
00:22:58,290 --> 00:23:02,460
You will have to come with us. You are a suspect for Yun Yeong Gil's murder.

279
00:23:02,460 --> 00:23:06,650
You have the right to be silent, and you have a right to an attorney.

280
00:23:10,640 --> 00:23:11,610
Breaking news.

281
00:23:11,610 --> 00:23:15,730
At around 2 p.m. today, Mr. Nam, a man in his 30s, who was appointed to the permanent post of Conductor,

282
00:23:15,730 --> 00:23:19,800
was arrested without a warrant as a suspect for the murder of Mr. Yun,

283
00:23:19,800 --> 00:23:22,710
who died in Sinyeong Philharmonic's building.

284
00:23:22,710 --> 00:23:24,950
Two men are involved in a fierce physical fight.

285
00:23:24,950 --> 00:23:28,320
And one of them pushes the other forcefully.

286
00:23:28,320 --> 00:23:31,970
The police used this video as evidence

287
00:23:31,970 --> 00:23:36,340
and, after investigation, applied for an arrest warrant.

288
00:23:36,340 --> 00:23:39,750
Then why are you looking for the evidence that Yun Yeong Gil hid?

289
00:23:39,750 --> 00:23:42,700
You are afraid that your face is recorded on that.

290
00:23:42,700 --> 00:23:45,610
Because you ran over a living person with a car.

291
00:23:45,610 --> 00:23:47,950
Why did you kill him?

292
00:23:47,950 --> 00:23:50,630
He didn't know anything.

293
00:23:50,630 --> 00:23:54,180
Even if he saw your face, he wouldn't have done anything.

294
00:23:54,180 --> 00:23:58,450
Don't act big, when you're the one who doesn't know anything.

295
00:23:58,450 --> 00:24:03,010
Why it was me getting out of the car? Was it me who was doing this to them?

296
00:24:03,010 --> 00:24:06,590
He asked if other people knew that I'm going around doing such things.

297
00:24:06,590 --> 00:24:08,750
He asked me while smirking!

298
00:24:08,750 --> 00:24:11,770
Is that why you killed him?

299
00:24:11,770 --> 00:24:14,230
Yes. I killed him. Why?

300
00:24:14,230 --> 00:24:17,190
Going to throw me in prison or something?

301
00:25:03,240 --> 00:25:05,710
What is in that ballpoint pen, anyway?

302
00:25:05,710 --> 00:25:08,230
The money that Professor Kang has embezzled from the college,

303
00:25:08,230 --> 00:25:11,300
small and large, everything.

304
00:25:23,070 --> 00:25:26,170
8/19/2018

305
00:25:26,900 --> 00:25:31,360
Kim Ian, 2/28/1991 - 8/19/2018

306
00:25:31,360 --> 00:25:34,740
8/19/2018

307
00:26:00,850 --> 00:26:03,940
2018.08.19

308
00:27:08,160 --> 00:27:10,550
Are you alright?

309
00:27:26,110 --> 00:27:28,140
It's dangerous!

310
00:27:41,710 --> 00:27:43,460
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

311
00:27:43,460 --> 00:27:45,550
I'm sorry!

312
00:27:49,950 --> 00:27:52,180
Run away.

313
00:27:53,360 --> 00:27:54,830
I won't leave you.

314
00:27:54,830 --> 00:27:57,210
You have to run away.

315
00:27:57,210 --> 00:28:00,940
I will not leave you alone!

316
00:28:09,010 --> 00:28:11,160
I can't. I can't.

317
00:28:11,160 --> 00:28:13,470
Please, please...

318
00:28:13,470 --> 00:28:16,380
Think straight, Hong Yi Yeong!

319
00:28:16,380 --> 00:28:18,630
Keep your mind focused and look at me.

320
00:28:21,170 --> 00:28:23,460
Listen to me well.

321
00:28:23,460 --> 00:28:28,190
From now on, just run towards wherever you see light.

322
00:28:28,190 --> 00:28:31,550
And when you see anyone, report this right away.

323
00:28:31,550 --> 00:28:32,900
Got it?

324
00:28:32,900 --> 00:28:35,480
I don't want to.

325
00:28:39,290 --> 00:28:45,370
I'm sorry for dragging you here when you didn't want to come.

326
00:28:46,790 --> 00:28:53,160
I told you there was something I couldn't tell you before.

327
00:28:56,000 --> 00:29:01,120
It would be great to see you again, but I'm not sure I can do that.

328
00:29:03,670 --> 00:29:10,630
I don't know how you feel, but I liked you so much.

329
00:29:10,630 --> 00:29:12,910
No, no.

330
00:29:12,910 --> 00:29:16,430
Don't say such things.

331
00:29:20,950 --> 00:29:24,550
I'm alright, so you go now.

332
00:29:24,550 --> 00:29:26,340
Hurry.

333
00:29:29,860 --> 00:29:32,130
Hurry and go!

334
00:31:18,010 --> 00:31:24,950
Timing and Subtitles by the Sing To Me Team @ viki
